-- Companies Plan 53 Shale Gas Wells in Poland in 2012, Rp.pl Says
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-04-10T05:50:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/companies-plan-53-shale-gas-wells-in-poland-in-2012-rp-pl-says.html
Companies including  Chevron Corp. (CVX) ,
 Talisman Energy Inc. (TLM)  and  Eni SpA (ENI)  are drilling 14 shale gas
exploration wells in Poland, while another 39 are planned for
2012, Rzeczpospolia reported, citing data from the Environment
Ministry.  Eighteen wells had been drilled by the end of last month,
according to the Warsaw-based daily newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
